items.title: China slow-walks U.S. soybean purchases as stockpiles hit multi-year highs, undermining Trump’s trade deal claims
items.description: China will likely "slow-roll soybean purchases to bait the Trump administration into prolonged negotiations," an analyst says.

items.title: Trump tariffs are helping drive U.S. beef prices to new highs
items.description: President Trump's tariffs are adding to higher beef prices, along with drought and parasites in a stressed U.S. beef supply chain.

items.title: September jobs report will be out Thursday as first data since shutdown starts to trickle out
items.description: The departments of Labor and Commerce had not posted revised schedules as of Friday morning, but updates are expected soon.

items.title: Atlanta Fed President Bostic says he'll leave position when his term expires in February
items.description: Atlanta Federal Reserve President Raphael Bostic said Wednesday he will be leaving his position when his term expires in February.

items.title: The shutdown put jobs and inflation data on hold. Here's when it could be back — and what it might say
items.description: Economic data releases — payroll and jobs reports, CPI and PPI — have lagged during the government shutdown and likely will take some time to get roll...
